        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 25 at 2:40PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 239 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Donner Peak, or near Soda Springs, moving east at
5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Prosser Creek Reservoir, Donner Peak, Independence Lake, Northstar,
Glenshire-Devonshire Cdp, Truckee, Northstar Ski Area, Ca 89 At
Nevada-Sierra Co Line, Upper Little Truckee Campground, Granite Flat
Campground, Lakeside Campground, Ca 89 At Placer-Nevada Co Line,
Alpine Meadows Campground, Hobart Mills, Truckee-Tahoe Airport, and
Donner Memorial Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
